The paper proposes a method for generating interpretable explanations for predictions made by Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) on graph-based machine learning tasks. This falls under the broad category of machine learning, specifically in the subfield of graph-based machine learning. The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques and mutual information, which are commonly used in the subfields of artificial intelligence and natural language processing (NLP), respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of GNNs for image classification, which falls under the subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of GNNs for identifying important graph structures, which could fall under the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
